# Adept LLM Modelfile — Phase 1 (01-02).
#
# Bakes the tight Phase-1 context window + Gemma 4 sampling params onto the
# resolved base tag. FROM uses ${OLLAMA_MODEL} so there is no hardcoded gemma
# tag here either — generate the pinned model by substituting the env var:
#
#   set -a && . ./.env && set +a
#   envsubst '${OLLAMA_MODEL}' < ollama/Modelfile \
#     | docker compose exec -T ollama ollama create adept-gemma -f -
#
# (OLLAMA_MODEL is resolved by ollama/pull-and-pin.sh; rung 1 = gemma4:e4b-it-q4_K_M.)
FROM ${OLLAMA_MODEL}

# Context window pinned to the measured Phase-4 worst case. Ollama PRE-ALLOCATES
# the full num_ctx KV cache upfront, so every extra 1k is reserved VRAM against
# the 16GB floor — num_ctx is a DIRECT VRAM cost, not a free ceiling.
#
# Phase-4 accounting (the frozen prefix is [persona] + [KB brief] + [history] + [turn]):
#   persona            ~250 tok   (render_prompt base, agent/persona.py)
#   KB brief budget    ~1500 tok  (BRIEF_TOKEN_BUDGET, agent/kb/distill.py)
#   max history window ~5000 tok  (multi-turn spoken context)
#   headroom           ~1440 tok  (turn tokens + slack)
#   ----------------------------------------------------------------
#   total              ~8190 tok  → 8192 covers the worst case; KEPT (not inflated).
#
# These are COUPLED constants — num_ctx tracks BRIEF_TOKEN_BUDGET (distill.py) and
# KB_MAX_TOKENS/KB_WARN_TOKENS (parse.py); raising one without the others either
# wastes VRAM or busts the frozen-prefix budget. q8_0 KV quant + flash-attn (the
# compose env OLLAMA_KV_CACHE_TYPE=q8_0 / OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION=1) HALVE the KV
# memory, which is what makes this num_ctx affordable inside the 16GB floor.
# The operator confirms the REAL distilled-brief token count via Proof C in
# 04-KB-VERIFY.md and bumps this only to a measured value if 8192 ever overflows.
# HOT-PATH NOTE (04-04): the agent (`/v1/chat` via with_ollama) and the distiller
# (`/api/generate`) load the BASE tag ${OLLAMA_MODEL}, NOT this `adept-gemma` model,
# so this PARAMETER does NOT reach the runtime on the hot path. The effective
# context there is enforced by the compose `ollama` service env
# (OLLAMA_CONTEXT_LENGTH=8192 + OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL=1). This PARAMETER documents the
# same budget and governs `adept-gemma` only if it is ever created (e.g. for the
# VRAM validator).
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192

# Gemma 4 recommended sampling (steady trainer voice tuned later).
PARAMETER temperature 1.0
PARAMETER top_p 0.95
PARAMETER top_k 64

# Thinking/reasoning mode is DISABLED to protect TTFT and first-sentence TTS
# streaming. Gemma 4 thinking is request-driven (Ollama `think: false`), so the
# warmup + agent callers pass think=false rather than the model needing a
# template-level <|think|> strip. ollama/warmup.py asserts no <think> preamble.
#
# Known Ollama bug #15260: `think=false` + `format` (structured JSON) silently
# drops the format constraint for gemma4. NOT a Phase 1 blocker (no structured
# output yet) — flagged here for the Phase 4 KB-distillation work, which may
# want JSON output and must work around #15260.
